The course begins with an overview of the structure of the Estonian language in the context of language learning, also introducing linguistic terminology. The two advanced Estonian language courses form a block that supports students' studies in Estonian in any chosen major. Second course in the spring semester.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To start giving an overview of the structure of Estonian in the context of language learning. To introduce the terminology of linguistics. The two courses of  Estonian for Advanced constitute a block that support the student's studies in any chosen specialty.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  By the end of the course the student: a) can use the basics of morphology in text production; b) uses the principle of analogy for inflecting words; c) takes into account the relations between cases in text production; d) uses non-finite constructions and uninflected words suitable for the given context; e) can convert numbers in the text into numerals; f) can find information about parts of speech, inflectional patterns and meaning in The Dictionary of Standard Estonian (ÕS).
